notes.note:
Spoke with customer's dad. He claims the vehicle was never over revved. He claims that the bottom end failure occurred due to a part being dropped into the engine. I told him we don't cover damage due to contamination. He then said the Toyota dealer told him that they were declining the claim, not because of over revving but because, prior to the customer purchasing, someone did an upper oil pan repair, botched that job, which caused the oil pan to fail and damaged the engine. I again confirmed that previous poor workmanship, especially prior to purchase, is not covered. 
Toyota is quoting a used engine and labour at $4600.00. A.H.
